The cortical fibers of the facial nerve proper originate from the lower third of the motor strip 
They course in the genu of the internal capsule and the middle third of the cerebral peduncle  supplying the seventh nucleus in the lower pons 
The supranuclear innervation is bilateral to the muscles of the forehead and eyes but only contralateral to the muscles of the lower part of the face 
This accounts for the sparing of the upper facial muscles with a contralateral cortical lesion 
